org.bubblecloud.zigbee.network.discovery

Class ImportingQueue

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.bubblecloud.zigbee.network.discovery.ImportingQueue

  • public class ImportingQueue
extends java.lang.Object
    Implements a discovery queue. When the discovery system detects a new node it is added to the ImportingQueue to be processed by the EndpointBuilder.

    The queue is implemented as a First In First Out (FIFO) queue. Entries are added to the beginning of the queue (with push(org.bubblecloud.zigbee.network.packet.ZToolAddress16, org.bubblecloud.zigbee.network.packet.ZToolAddress64)) and removed from the end (with pop()).

    Duplicate entries are not added to the queue.

    Since:
    0.1.0
    Author:
    Stefano "Kismet" Lenzi, Francesco Furfari, Chris Jackson
